        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-15T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93/1–747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-15T16:00:00-05:00">January 15, 1947—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. Matter discussed informally with Navy which states necessary processing in
                    field applications by Marine personnel will consume considerable amount time and
                    therefore no departure dependents contemplated immediate future. (Embtel 36, Jan
                    7) Problem will be presented General Marshall his arrival Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
